---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import BackToHome from '../components/BackToHome.astro';
import PageNav from '../components/PageNav.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="10 Bitcoin Facts" pageColor="#FFEA00">
  <Header />

  <main class="main-content">
    <PageHeader title="10 Bitcoin Facts" color="#FFEA00" textColor="#111" />

    <div class="content-container">
      <Breadcrumbs current="10 Bitcoin Facts" />
      <p><strong class="page-colored-strong">Bitcoin and Crypto are different things.</strong></p>
      <p>When people learn the difference they understand why Bitcoin is so special.</p>
      <div class="facts-list">
        <div class="fact-item">
          <p>There will only ever be 21 million bitcoin.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact-item">
          <p>No one knows who invented Bitcoin.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact-item">
          <p>
            Bitcoin is not a company, it doesn't have a CEO or leader, and can't go bankrupt.
            Bitcoin has nothing to do with the NASDAQ, or any political party, or a specific
            country.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact-item">
          <p>
            Bitcoin was inspired by decades of research into money and cryptography.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact-item">
          <p>
            Bitcoin was designed to help everyday people by preserving their wealth and making their
            payments impossible to block.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact-item">
          <p>
            It's incredibly difficult to take or steal someone's bitcoin when they understand how it
            works.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact-item">
          <p>
            Bitcoin mining creates new bitcoin. It's not solving complex math problems. It's more
            like a lottery that requires electricity to play, this makes bitcoin hard to produce, or
            fake, and keeps it scarce. <strong class="page-colored-strong"
              >Bitcoin is backed by energy.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact-item">
          <p>
            Every four years the amount of new bitcoin that can be created is halved. Most of it
            already exists.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact-item">
          <p>
            Bitcoin (with big B) refers to the entire Bitcoin payments system (the protocol), while
            bitcoin (with small b) refers to the currency/money that you can buy, use and sell.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact-item">
          <p>
            bitcoin is a really bad money for criminals or money launderers to use. It can easily be
            tracked.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <BackToHome />
    </div>
    <PageNav />
  </main>

  <style>
    .main-content {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: var(--content-width);
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 var(--spacing-md);
      box-sizing: border-box;
      flex: 1;
      background: #000; /* Pure black background */
      min-height: 100%;
    }

    .content-container {
      background: #111;
      border: 1px solid #444;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
      color: #e0e0e0;
      padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    }

    h1 {
      color: #fff;
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
      padding-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
      border-bottom: 2px solid #444;
      font-size: 2rem;
      line-height: 1.3;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .facts-list {
      width: 100%;
      margin: var(--spacing-md) 0 var(--spacing-xl) 0;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .fact-item {
      padding: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #444;
      transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
    }

    .fact-item:first-child {
      border-top: 1px solid #444;
    }

    .fact-item:last-child {
      border-bottom: none;
    }

    .fact-item:hover {
      border-bottom-color: var(--page-color, #ffea00);
    }

    .fact-item p {
      color: #e0e0e0;
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 400;
    }

    .fact-item strong {
      color: var(--page-color, #ffea00);
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .warning-box {
      background: #fff !important;
      border: 2px solid #ff4444 !important;
      position: relative;
      margin: 2rem 0;
    }

    .warning-box .fact-content {
      color: #000 !important;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    }

    .warning-box .fact-number {
      background: #ff4444 !important;
      color: #fff !important;
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .warning-box::before {
      content: '⚠️';
      position: absolute;
      right: 1rem;
      top: 50%;
      transform: translateY(-50%);
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    @media (min-width: 768px) {
      .fact-grid {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        margin: 0 var(--spacing-md) var(--spacing-lg) var(--spacing-md);
        border-radius: 8px;
      }

      .content-container::before {
        left: var(--spacing-md);
        right: var(--spacing-md);
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 1.75rem;
      }

      ol {
        padding-left: var(--spacing-md);
      }
    }

    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      * {
        transition: none !important;
        animation: none !important;
      }

      .fact-item:hover {
        border-bottom-color: #444 !important;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
